originalText.text: Neil is truly- hands down the best massage therapist I’ve ever been to, and I’ve been to a lot, all over the US.  I stumbled on his page via Google and am so lucky that I did. Neil is very responsive and an excellent communicator. He is also incredibly kind, empathetic and professional. I went to him with a neck/back injury from an auto accident and now feel immensely better from the work and time he gave to me. If I could recommend the whole of New York City to Neil, I would. No need to scroll further- you’ve found your guy.

originalText.text: I have been seeing Neil regularly for over six years now, and I am still constantly blown away by how knowledgeable and thorough he is in his work. As someone who relies on my body for my career, I have had my fair share of injuries and muscle imbalances and Neil always listens, asks questions and works through my problem areas, leaving me feel like a new person when I leave. I could not give him enough praise!!

originalText.text:
I've been going to Neil for prenatal massages throughout my pregnancy and look forward to every single session. I'd highly recommend him to anyone expecting.

Neil has helped me navigate all the unexpected aches that crop up as pregnancy progresses on top of chronic shoulder pain. He uses his wealth of knowledge and experience to tailor his work to address what is most helpful. As a new mom, Neil's skills, thoughtfulness, calm demeanor, and beautiful studio are an oasis amongst all the stress of pregnancy.

originalText.text: After my session with Neil, I feel like a totally new person. Not because it was the week of my birthday, but mentally and physically at ease. In some beauty one have to feel it, if you try to put words into it, it may change and Neil touch is more than that. I told friends and coworkers to just try a massage with Neil, because for me that was one of the best gifts I gave to myself. I am so grateful for that!

originalText.text: I’m convinced Neil is one of the best massage therapist in the city. He’s not only amazing at his job, but he’s also a kind and caring human. He’ll listen to your concerns and issues and explain what he is doing. I went to see Neil on my third trimester when expecting my little boy. I had severe back pain, hip pain, and pelvic pain. I had been to chiropractic care and physical therapy, but having a prenatal massage with Neil was the one thing that actually gave me substantial relief. You can feel how he untangles your body structures from tension. It’s amazing! Can’t recommend him enough.
